# =============================================================================
# Permoney Environment Variables — Template
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values. NEVER commit `.env`.
#
# Loading: Prisma does NOT auto-load .env. The project uses `prisma.config.ts`
# which calls `import "dotenv/config"` to bridge env vars into the Prisma CLI.
# Application runtime (Vite+) auto-loads .env via Vite's standard mechanism.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Database (REQUIRED) — see ADR-0003 (docs/adr/0003-production-database.md)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LibSQL / SQLite connection string consumed by both:
#   1. Prisma CLI (migrations, generate)
#   2. Runtime (`@prisma/adapter-libsql` in src/server/db.server.ts)
#
# `db.server.ts` resolves the adapter config by URL scheme:
#   • `file:`                              → local embedded SQLite (no token)
#   • `libsql://` / `https://` / `wss://`  → Turso remote (token REQUIRED)
# A misconfigured remote URL without a token crashes at boot with a precise
# error — by design. Failing fast > opaque 401 on first query.
#
# ── Local development (embedded SQLite file) ────────────────────────────────
DATABASE_URL="file:./prisma/dev.db"
#
# ── Production (Turso managed libSQL edge replicas) ─────────────────────────
# Provision once with the Turso CLI:
#   $ turso db create permoney-prod --group <region>
#   $ turso db show permoney-prod --url               # → libsql://...
#   $ turso db tokens create permoney-prod            # → JWT
# Then export both into your prod env (Fly secrets / Vercel env / etc.):
# DATABASE_URL="libsql://permoney-prod-<your-org>.turso.io"
# DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN="<jwt-from-turso-cli>"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth (FUTURE — not yet wired, see ADRs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AUTH_SECRET="<openssl rand -base64 32>"
# AUTH_TRUST_HOST=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Observability (FUTURE)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SENTRY_DSN=""
# SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT="development"
